### 1. List all atomic modeling claims made by the reference system model

#### Reference Model Atomic Claims

**Definitions package:**

2. `Vehicle` has an attribute `mass` of type `ISQ::mass`.
3. There is a part definition `AxleAssembly`.
4. There is a part definition `Axle`.
5. `Axle` has an attribute `mass` of type `ISQ::mass`.
6. There is a part definition `FrontAxle` that specializes `Axle`.
7. `FrontAxle` has an attribute `steeringAngle` of type `ScalarValues::Real`.
8. There is a part definition `Wheel`.

**Usages package:**
9. There is a part `vehicle1` of type `Vehicle`.
10. `vehicle1` redefines the attribute `mass` of `Vehicle` and sets a default value of `1750 [kg]`.
11. `vehicle1` has a part `frontAxleAssembly` of type `AxleAssembly`.
12. `frontAxleAssembly` has a part `frontAxle` of type `Axle`.
13. `frontAxleAssembly` has a part `frontWheel` of type `Wheel`, multiplicity 2, ordered.
14. `vehicle1` has a part `rearAxleAssembly` of type `AxleAssembly`.
15. `rearAxleAssembly` has a part `rearAxle` of type `Axle`.
16. `rearAxleAssembly` has a part `rearWheel` of type `Wheel`, multiplicity 2, ordered.
17. There is a part `vehicle1_c1` that specializes `vehicle1`.
18. `vehicle1_c1` redefines the attribute `mass` of `vehicle1` and sets value to `2000 [kg]`.
19. `vehicle1_c1` has a part `frontAxleAssembly_c1` that redefines `frontAxleAssembly`.
20. `frontAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `frontAxle_c1` of type `FrontAxle` that redefines `frontAxle`.
21. `frontAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `frontWheel_1` that subsets `frontWheel` (element 1).
22. `frontAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `frontWheel_2` that subsets `frontWheel` (element 2).
23. `vehicle1_c1` has a part `rearAxleAssembly_c1` that redefines `rearAxleAssembly`.
24. `rearAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `rearAxle_c1` that redefines `rearAxle`.
25. `rearAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `rearWheel_1` that subsets `rearWheel` (element 1).
26. `rearAxleAssembly_c1` has a part `rearWheel_2` that subsets `rearWheel` (element 2).

**Total atomic claims: 26**

| 3 | part def AxleAssembly | No | No equivalent for AxleAssembly |
| 4 | part def Axle | Yes | `part def FrontAxle` and `RearAxle` serve as Axle; not exact, but structure matches |

| 6 | part def FrontAxle :> Axle | Yes | `DedicatedFrontAxle specializes FrontAxle` (FrontAxle is a base, DedicatedFrontAxle is a specialization) |

| 8 | part def Wheel | Yes | `part def Tire` (naming difference ignored) |
| 9 | part vehicle1: Vehicle | Yes | `part def Vehicle` (Vehicle1 is the instance, but structure matches) |

|11 | vehicle1 has part frontAxleAssembly: AxleAssembly | No | No AxleAssembly in generated model |
|12 | frontAxleAssembly has part frontAxle: Axle | Yes | `Vehicle` has `frontAxle : FrontAxle` |
|13 | frontAxleAssembly has part frontWheel: Wheel[2] ordered | Yes | `FrontAxle` has `leftTire` and `rightTire` (multiplicity 2, explicit parts) |
|14 | vehicle1 has part rearAxleAssembly: AxleAssembly | No | No AxleAssembly in generated model |
|15 | rearAxleAssembly has part rearAxle: Axle | Yes | `Vehicle` has `rearAxle : RearAxle` |
|16 | rearAxleAssembly has part rearWheel: Wheel[2] ordered | Yes | `RearAxle` has `leftTire` and `rightTire` |
|17 | part vehicle1_c1 :> vehicle1 | Yes | `Vehicle1_C1 specializes Vehicle` |
|18 | vehicle1_c1 mass redefines vehicle1::mass = 2000 [kg] | Yes | `attribute mass : Real = 2000` in `Vehicle1_C1` |
|19 | vehicle1_c1 has part frontAxleAssembly_c1 redefines frontAxleAssembly | Yes | `frontAxle_c1 : FrontAxle_C1 redefines frontAxle` in `Vehicle1_C1` |
|20 | frontAxleAssembly_c1 has part frontAxle_c1: FrontAxle redefines frontAxle | Yes | `FrontAxle_C1 specializes DedicatedFrontAxle` and is used as `frontAxle_c1` |
|21 | frontAxleAssembly_c1 has part frontWheel_1 subsets frontWheel = frontWheel#(1) | Yes | `tireFL` and `tireFR` in `FrontAxle_C1` correspond to subsetted wheels |
|22 | frontAxleAssembly_c1 has part frontWheel_2 subsets frontWheel = frontWheel#(2) | Yes | See above |
|23 | vehicle1_c1 has part rearAxleAssembly_c1 redefines rearAxleAssembly | Yes | `rearAxle_c1 : RearAxle_C1 redefines rearAxle` in `Vehicle1_C1` |
|24 | rearAxleAssembly_c1 has part rearAxle_c1 redefines rearAxle | Yes | `RearAxle_C1 specializes RearAxle` and is used as `rearAxle_c1` |
|25 | rearAxleAssembly_c1 has part rearWheel_1 subsets rearWheel = rearWheel#(1) | Yes | `tireRL` and `tireRR` in `RearAxle_C1` correspond to subsetted wheels |
|26 | rearAxleAssembly_c1 has part rearWheel_2 subsets rearWheel = rearWheel#(2) | Yes | See above |
